name: Heart of Azeroth

main_spell_tooltip.description: Focus excess Azerite energy into the Heart of Azeroth, then expel that energy outward, dealing 829 Fire damage to all enemies in front of you over 2.7 sec. Castable while moving.

passive_spell_tooltip.description:
Your damaging spells and abilities grant you 2 Haste for 4 sec, stacking up to 10 times. This Haste is lost if you stop using spells or abilities against the initial target.

When you have no stacks of Focused Energy, generate 3 stacks from your first damaging spell or ability.

Your spells and abilities have a chance to increase you and 2 other allies' Haste by 5 for 8 sec and reduce the cooldown of you and 2 other allies' currently slotted Major Essence by 1.0 sec.

Unique:  Corruption Resistance increased by 10.
Your spells and abilities have a chance to cauterize your target for 398 Fire damage over 10 sec or to heal an ally for 398 over 10 sec, stacking up to 3 times.
Every 1-25 sec, a Lifeblood Shard erupts from the nearby ground for 18 sec.

spells.description: Equip: Harnesses the energy of raw Azerite, awakening exceptional pieces of armor that possess latent powers.

description: A living symbol of hope, borne by the champions of a dying planet. The fate of Azeroth will be shared by all her children.

spells.description:
Use: Take what is rightfully yours, gorging on your target's essence to deal 3.6 million Shadow damage and healing you for 546,044 over 2 sec. Damage and healing increased based on the target's missing health.

Cooldown reduced by 60 sec if this effect kills the target. (2 Min Cooldown)
Use: Receive cryptic instructions from somewhere in the Twisting Nether to reveal your next task. It's probably nothing, so complete it to gain 12,053 Agility for 15 sec.  (1 Min 30 Sec Cooldown)
Equip: Your attacks have a very high chance to contaminate your target with industrial runoff up to 25 times, dealing 2,038 Shadow damage per stack every 3 sec until their demise.
